3049	[Sq3 --- composition coherence of \(\mathtt{sheafifyTensorUnitIso}\) (D3$'$)]
3050	  \label{lem:sheafify_tensor_unit_iso_comp}
3051	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.sheafifyTensorUnitIso_comp}
3052	  \uses{def:sheafify_tensor_unit_iso, lem:sheafify_tensor_unit_iso_hom_eq_prime, lem:toringcatsheafhom_comp_hom_reconcile}
3053	  With notation as in \cref{lem:pullback_tensor_map_basechange}, write \(F^{\mathrm p}_\bullet =
3054	  \mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi'_\bullet\) for the presheaf-level pullback and \(a_\bullet\) for
3055	  sheafification. The tensor/unit reconciliation \(\mathtt{sheafifyTensorUnitIso}\) of the
3056	  \emph{composite} \(h \circ f\), evaluated on \(F^{\mathrm p}_{h\circ f}M.\mathrm{val}\) and
3057	  \(F^{\mathrm p}_{h\circ f}N.\mathrm{val}\), agrees --- after transport through the presheaf
3058	  pullback pseudofunctoriality identification
3059	  \(\mathtt{PrPbComp} = \mathtt{PresheafOfModules.pullbackComp}\,\varphi'_f\,\varphi'_h\)
3060	  (\cref{lem:toringcatsheafhom_comp_hom_reconcile} licenses the composite ring map) --- with the
3061	  \(f\)-instance carried by \(h^{*}\) followed by the \(h\)-instance on the pulled-back arguments.
3062	  Concretely, the \(\mathtt{hom}\) legs of the two presentations are equal as morphisms in
3063	  \(\Scheme.\mathtt{Modules}\,Z\).
3064	\end{lemma}
3065	\begin{proof}
3066	  \uses{def:sheafify_tensor_unit_iso, lem:sheafify_tensor_unit_iso_hom_eq_prime}
3067	  By \cref{lem:sheafify_tensor_unit_iso_hom_eq_prime} each \(\mathtt{sheafifyTensorUnitIso}.\mathrm{hom}\)
3068	  is a single \(a.\mathrm{map}\) of a \(\mathtt{tensorHom}\) of sheafification-unit components
3069	  \(\eta_P \otimes \eta_Q\), kept inside one monoidal structure on \(\mathtt{PresheafOfModules}\).
3070	  The composite-vs-interleaved discrepancy is therefore the image, under \(a_Z.\mathrm{map}\), of the
3071	  naturality of the sheafification unit \(\eta\) against the presheaf identification \(\mathtt{PrPbComp}\),
3072	  one tensor factor at a time; bifunctoriality of \(\otimes\) (the interchange law) recombines the two
3073	  single-factor squares into the asserted equality. Because the composite carries the
3074	  \(\mathtt{Sheaf.val}\,Z\) carrier spelling, the rewrite of \(\mathtt{PrPbComp}\) into the
3075	  \(\mathtt{tensorHom}\) is performed with \(\mathtt{erw}\).
3076	\end{proof}
